# File: tests/features/element-targeted-scrolling.feature
#
# Generated from: .claude/specs/feature-element-targeted-scrolling-inner-containers/requirements.md
# Issue: #182

Feature: Element-targeted scrolling for inner containers
  As a developer or AI agent automating pages with scrollable inner containers
  I want to scroll specific elements by CSS selector or accessibility UID
  So that I can navigate content within nested scrollable containers without resorting to js exec

  Background:
    Given a Chrome session is connected

  # --- Happy Path ---

  Scenario: Scroll inner container by CSS selector (AC1)
    Given a page with a scrollable container matching CSS selector ".stage"
    When I run interact scroll with selector ".stage" and direction "down"
    Then the command exits with code 0
    And the JSON output "scrolled.y" is greater than 0
    And the JSON output "position.y" is greater than 0

  # --- Alternative Path ---

  Scenario: Scroll inner container by UID (AC2)
    Given a page with a scrollable container
    And I have taken a page snapshot
    And the scrollable container has a UID assigned
    When I run interact scroll with the container UID and direction "down" and amount 300
    Then the command exits with code 0
    And the JSON output "scrolled.y" is approximately 300

  # --- Error Handling ---

  Scenario: Error on non-scrollable target (AC3)
    Given a page with a non-scrollable element "#static-div"
    When I run interact scroll with selector "#static-div" and direction "down"
    Then the command exits with a non-zero code
    And stderr contains a JSON error with message matching "not scrollable"

  Scenario: Selector and UID flags conflict with each other (AC4)
    When I run interact scroll with both selector ".stage" and uid "s1"
    Then the command exits with a non-zero code
    And stderr contains a JSON error about conflicting arguments

  # --- Smooth Scroll ---

  Scenario: Smooth scroll works with targeted containers (AC5)
    Given a page with a scrollable container matching CSS selector ".panel"
    When I run interact scroll with selector ".panel" and direction "down" and smooth
    Then the command exits with code 0
    And the JSON output "scrolled.y" is greater than 0

  # --- Direction Coverage ---

  Scenario Outline: All four scroll directions work with targeted containers (AC6)
    Given a page with a scrollable container that has both horizontal and vertical overflow
    When I run interact scroll with selector ".panel" and direction "<direction>"
    Then the command exits with code 0
    And the JSON output "<scroll_field>" is not zero

    Examples:
      | direction | scroll_field |
      | down      | scrolled.y   |
      | up        | scrolled.y   |
      | right     | scrolled.x   |
      | left      | scrolled.x   |
